The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 23 November is 1,314,888 (2,336 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 November, there were 135,474 new confirmed cases (240.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 November, there were 153,437 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 12% (17,963 fewer cases).
